41.raw:
Meeting: Date & Time: 14 June 2015, 4:00PM
Meeting Memo:
- Yim Tong is an Associate Director at AIGF. She studied in the UK (LSE), then worked for UBS in Hong Kong (6 months) and then moved back to SG to join AIGF (Feb 2015).
- AIGF is a fund created in conjunction with Mitsubishi (trading company), CIMB Group and Development Bank of Japan. The fund size as of early 2015 is USD130m. It is an independent fund, therefore they invest in a variety of industries and sectors in SEA (focus on Indonesia, Malaysia, Singapore and Vietnam), which are not necessarily linked to Japan. The only areas they do not invest in are: Real Estate, Infrastructure and Upstream Resources. They target mid-size companies (USD15m-USD35m)
- The team has 6 members (3 Japanese) handling 15-30 simultaneous projects (mainly sourcing and due diligence since they do not have any portfolio company yet).
- Private Equity is a new field for her and has started using Expert Networks only recently. She was interested to understand the different ways she can leverage our services - although had some concerns over background checks, especially the reliability of sources and conflict of interest.
I shared with her our Infosheet and the summary of our offerings across the deal cycle.
She said there are many projects they might need help with so will stay in touch.

parsed.Last Meeting:

41.raw:
Meeting: Date & Time: 25 June 2015, 2:00PM
Meeting Memo:
- Kenta has been with MBK Partners for over 3 years. Prior to that, he worked at McKinsey (Tokyo) in the Strategy group, working on many overseas projects in Germany, Hong Kong and US. 
- At MBK Partners he has been involved in portfolio management of Tasaki (pearl manufacturer), Komeda (cafe chain) and USJ (theme park). He is currently assisting the USJ exit process. 
- He mentioned that MBK Partners has been very successful in developing strategies to turnaround profit loss and accelerate growth for Tasaki and USJ. For Tasaki, they implemented a new marketing strategy to transform the brand image from ‘conservative’ and for older generation to ‘stylish' and aimed at younger generation, resulting in exceptional returns. For USJ, they implemented seasonal events promotions (such as Easter special, Summer special) which had a good reception among families and youngsters. 
- MBK Partners in Tokyo does not have any contract with any other expert network and most of the team members are not very familiar with these kind of services, however they are willing to try.
- Kenta kindly suggested to introduce us to his friends at Goldman Sachs and KKR. Maria will try to coordinate an introduction to see if Peggy can meet them in July in Tokyo.
- Kenta used to be a professional singer (back up singer for popular boy band EXILE) and is a keen marathon runner, participating in pro-level marathons in Africa, Europe and Japan. He is also an avid traveller and visited many countries in South America and Africa for months during college years.
